defaultSouthWest
default was established in 2001 as The South West 
defaultPublic Transport Users' Forum (SWPTUF) to promote the interests of public transport users in the South West of England (comprising the counties of Devon, Dorset, Gloucestershire and Somerset and the unitary authorities of Bath and North East Somerset, Bour
defaultnemouth, Bristol, Cornwall, North Somerset, Plymouth, Poole, South Gloucestershire, Swindon, Torbay and Wiltshire) - the Forum became a Community Interest Company, limited by guarantee, in August 2005. SWPTUF adopted the trading name of 
defaultTravelWatch
default 
defaultSouthWe
defaultst
default in June 2006 and the Community Interest Company changed name to 
defaultTravelWatch
default 
defaultSouthWest
default CIC in November 2008.
default&#xa0;
defaultMembership of the 
defaultTravelWatch
default 
defaultSouthWest
default CIC is open to every 'not-for-profit' organisation in the South West of England whose sole or principal 
defaultpurpose is to represent the users of any public transport service or to promote the development of public transport services - membership is also open to other 'not-for-profit' organisations' in the South West England who represent the interests of special
default and potential classes of public transport users e.g. the disabled or the elderly. TWSW currently has over one hundred affiliated organisations.
default&#xa0;
defaultTWSW, which is a social enterprise company, acts as an advocate for passengers to lobby for the improvement of
default public transport in the region and works closely with local authorities, local enterprise partnerships, business organisations and other stakeholder groups - with the dissolution of the former Rail Passengers Committee for Western England in July 2005, TW
defaultSW is the representative body for public transport users throughout the South West of England.
