default6. Despite the figures on car ownership within 
defaultsuper output areas, which show between 20 and 30% of residents not having access to a private car, there is a broad assumption that most rural residents who are economically active have access to one. Planning based on this assumption contributes to the li
defaultmited options for employment of young people in rural areas, and lower than expected levels of post-school training and qualifications.
